    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-04-05T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-04-05T05:00:00-05:00" n="693"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d693">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">751G.00/4–554: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_DCD1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dillon</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret<lb/>
                            <gloss target="#t_niact1">niact</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-04-05T11:00:00+01:00"
                            >April 5, 1954—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 5:11 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3711. Limit distribution. In connection with Embassy telegram 3710,<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d693fn1">Dated Apr. 5, <ref target="#pg_1236">p. 1236</ref>.</note>
                    <persName corresp="#p_BG1">Bidault</persName> told me that he is more convinced
                    than ever that Soviets very much desire a cease-fire and truce in Indochina
                    because of their deep concern of possible action by Chinese if fighting
                    continues.</p>
                <p>He said that Vinogradov<note n="2" xml:id="d693fn2">Sergey Aleksandrovich
                        Vinogradov, Soviet Ambassador in France.</note> came to see him again and
                    literally pleaded with him to arrange a truce with <persName corresp="#p_HCM1"
                        >Ho Chi-minh</persName>, saying that fighting in Indochina simply must
                    stop.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DCD1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dillon</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
